               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699">
                     <origPlace/>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Previously belonged to prince Dara Shikoh and subsequently passed into the imperial Mughal library.</p>
                     <p>RSPA 1-118 were presented to the Royal Society in January 1792 by Sir William and Lady Jones. According to Wilkins' catalogue, this MS was presented by Sir William Jones.</p>
                     <p>The Royal Society's collection of 280 Persian and Arabic, and 86 Sanskrit manuscripts were transferred to the India Office Library in 1876.</p>
                  </provenance>
